All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
ArrayBiterator
Implementation of SizedBiterator used to stream all values within a specified integer array representing indices in an order appropriate to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
Biterator
Implementation of Spliterator that is meant to be used in conjunction with BitSets.
BitSet
Represents a fixed number of bits stored within an internal long array, mapping positive integer indices to individual bits and facilitating the manipulation of those individual bits or ranges of bits, as well as retrieving their boolean values.
ConcurrentBitSet
Implementation of BitSet in which all methods capable of reading or writing the state of bits such as ConcurrentBitSet.getWord(int), ConcurrentBitSet.setWord(int, long), ConcurrentBitSet.andWord(int, long), ConcurrentBitSet.orWord(int, long), ConcurrentBitSet.xorWord(int, long) are delegated to atomic-operations.
DeadBiterator
Implementation of DensityBiterator used to stream the indices of dead bits within a BitSet, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
DensityBiterator
Implementation of Biterator used to allow parallel processing when the number of live indices is expensive to compute, but the density of them can be estimated in order to split efficiently.
DensityXOrShift
Implementation of XOrShift which generates bits with a specified Hamming-weight ratio using a sequence of bitwise AND and OR operations.
FunctionBiterator
Implementation of DensityBiterator that creates a stream of indices that represents which bits will be live after performing a FunctionBiterator.bitwiseFunction(long, long) between the words of 2 BitSets at the same word index.
FunctionBiterator.And
Implementation of FunctionBiterator used to stream the indices of bits that result in the live state after the AND operation, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
FunctionBiterator.Or
Implementation of FunctionBiterator used to stream the indices of bits that result in the live state after the OR operation, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
FunctionBiterator.XOr
Implementation of FunctionBiterator used to stream the indices of bits that result in the live state after the XOR operation, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
LiveBiterator
Implementation of DensityBiterator used to stream the indices of live bits within a BitSet, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
RangeBiterator
Implementation of SizedBiterator used to stream all indices of a specified range, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
SizedBiterator
Implementation of Biterator that is meant to be used when streaming a known number of indices.
XOrShift
Pseudo-random number generator using a modified version of the XORShift64 algorithm to generate uniform random numbers.
